        jTextPane1.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Arial", 0, 18)); // NOI18N
        jTextPane1.setText("1. River Rafting\nMany travelers visit Rishikesh just to enjoy an adrenaline-pumping experience of river rafting in the waters of Ganga River. Your trip to Rishikesh is incomplete without taking part in the river rafting sport that is organized by many different camping sites in this region. It is one of the best activities that you can do here and if you are an adventure junky then you shouldn’t miss out on this. You can enjoy it the most during the summer seasons as the chilly and holy water of the Ganga river is sure to refresh your body and mind. You should avoid river rafting during the monsoon season as the waves can be pretty dangerous during that time.\nAverage river rafting charges at Rishikesh: INR 400-1300. You can save a lot of money if you take these activities in the Rishikesh summer package.\nWhere to do river rafting in Rishikesh: Brahmpuri to Rishikesh, Shivpuri to Rishikesh, Marine Drive to Rishikesh, Kaudiyala\n\n2. Ganga Aarti\nIf you an aspiring photographer then the Ganga aarti is the thing that can give you the most picturesque moments. Ganga Aarti is one of the most celebrated events in Rishikesh, it is enjoyed by both travelers and locals alike. This grand religious ceremony consists of Ten priests, facing the riverside with diva stands. This ceremony is conducted every day at 5 pm by different priests. Your trip to Rishikesh is incomplete if you didn’t experience this beautiful moment of Hindu religion. Even if you consider yourself an atheist you should still at least give it a try just for the beauty and the peaceful vibes that you can get from it. You will find a lot of fans watching these priests and other devotees sing their hearts out.\nAverage charges for Ganga aarti: NA\nWhere to see Ganga aarti in Rishikesh: Parmarth Niketan Ashram\n\n3. Beach Camping\nThere are many campsites near the banks of ganga in Rishikesh. All of these campsites are organized by tour companies and you can enjoy great meals, bonfire and several other group activities with other travelers. In these campsites, you will get great meals and several amazing games. You can either spend your entire day laying around the beautiful view of the campsite or you can play beach volleyball with your friends. Many of these campsites also organise regular and guided tours to various places to visit in Rishikesh during summer. If you want to have a nice fun time with your friends then these campsites are the ideal place for you in Rishikesh.\nAverage camping charges at Rishikesh: INR 1,200 (per person per night package)\nWhere to do camping in Rishikesh: Aspen Adventures Camp, Camp AquaForest Rishikesh\n\n4. Morning Yoga\nBeing the Yoga capital of the world there are many places in Rishikesh offering Yoga classes. Even if you haven’t visited Rishikesh for Yoga you are bound to be caught up in the Yoga vibes that oozes from every corner of this region. Most of the Yoga ashrams in Rishikesh offer free Yoga classes to travelers and visitors, so if you have some spare time or just want to try your hand in beginner yoga classes then you should visit a Yoga ashram. We have heard many cases in which people who were not remotely interested in yoga practice become a regular yoga practitioner after taking a free class in the Yoga ashrams of the Rishikesh. If you just want to see the experts perform the Yoga asanas then you can head to the riverside early in the morning to see them in action.\nAverage yoga charges at Rishikesh: NA\nWhere to do yoga in Rishikesh: Anand Prakash Yoga Studio\n\n5. Flying Fox\nIf you are an adventure enthusiast then you may have heard of the Flying fox in Rishikesh. Rishikesh has one of the biggest flying fox routes in Asia. If you haven’t heard of it before then here is a quick overview for you: In flying fox, your body is tied through a harness, you will be at the seven meters height from the ground and go at the speed of 160km/hr. Most of the time it is done in a group of 3 people but if you want to do it alone you are free to do so. The minimum age requirement for taking part in flying fox is 12 and the minimum weight is 20 that goes all the way to 130kg. Flying Fox is among the best things to do in Rishikesh during summer.\nAverage charges for flying fox in Rishikesh: INR 1199-1399\nWhere to try flying fox in Rishikesh: Shivpuri");
